The config change in step 5 is because we want the segment split-committer to look like this:
```
    doCommitStart();
    url = uploadSegmentToDeepStore();
    if (url == null) { // upload failed, or no deep store configured
      if (tableConfig.commitEvenIfUploadFailed) {
        segmentUrlForCommitEnd = PEER_URL
      } else {
        throw CommitFailedException
      }
    } else {
      segmentUrilForCommitEnd = url
    }
    doCommitEnd();
```

The config is needed in order to decide the action when upload returns null url.

Another way to do it is to configure a new class in `StreamConfig` section and use that class to bypass deep-store. Them you can leave the main split-committer as is, and build another class that can be configured in.

Either way, you need a config.

